From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +1000
Subject: net: phy: realtek: mask RTL826x interrupt before hardware reset

rtl826x_config_init() toggles the PHY soft-reset via VEND1:0x145[0].
On power-on the RTL8261N asserts its interrupt pin during this reset
sequence before phylib has registered phy_interrupt. The kernel sees an
unhandled IRQ, fires "nobody cared", and permanently disables the line.
With the IRQ dead the PHY can never signal link-up, leaving the port
down on the first boot after a cold flash.

Silence the PHY interrupt output (VEND2:INER = 0, VEND1:0xE1[0] = 0)
before triggering the reset so the pin stays de-asserted until
rtl826x_config_intr() is called later by phylib.

--- a/drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek_main.c
@@ -2635,6 +2635,14 @@ static int rtl826x_config_init(struct phy_device *phydev)
 	unsigned int tries = 0;
 	int ret;

+	/* Suppress PHY interrupt output before the hardware reset below.
+	 * The RTL8261N asserts its interrupt pin during power-on reset, which
+	 * races with phylib registering phy_interrupt. If the IRQ fires first
+	 * the kernel disables it permanently. rtl826x_config_intr() will
+	 * re-enable the interrupt correctly once phylib is ready. */
+	phy_write_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, RTL826X_VND2_INER, 0);
+	phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND1, 0xE1, BIT(0), 0);
+
 	/* toggle reset */
 	ret = phy_modify_mmd_changed(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND1, 0x145, BIT(0), 1);
 	if (ret < 0)
